hopwatch is a ground-up TypeScript re-implementation of a SmokePing-style
network latency and packet-loss visualization tool. Its visual output
deliberately matches SmokePing's so that operators familiar with SmokePing
can read hopwatch charts without retraining.

No SmokePing or rrdtool source code has been copied into this project.
Algorithmic references that informed hopwatch's renderer:

- SmokePing's `smokecol()` grayscale band mapping
  (Smokeping.pm, author: Tobi Oetiker -- https://oss.oetiker.ch/smokeping/)

- rrdtool's AREA+STACK rendering approach for stacked loss-tinted median
  markers, and its axis/grid/dashing conventions
  (rrdtool, author: Tobi Oetiker -- https://oss.oetiker.ch/rrdtool/)

The short rotated "RRDTOOL / TOBI OETIKER" signature rendered along the
right edge of every chart is retained as attribution and homage to
Tobi Oetiker, whose work inspired hopwatch.

hopwatch is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Tobi Oetiker,
SmokePing, or rrdtool. It is an independent project.

Where fixture reference PNGs are included for visual-regression testing
purposes, they were produced by running SmokePing against public Internet
endpoints; no copyrighted SmokePing imagery or assets are distributed
beyond what operators of SmokePing would produce themselves.
